#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/semver.md:131
msgid "Prerelease bump rules:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/semver.md:133
msgid ""
"Bumping a stable version to `alpha`, `beta`, or `rc` first increments the "
"patch version, then enters the target channel starting from `.1`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/semver.md:135
msgid ""
"`prepatch`, `preminor`, and `premajor` start a fresh prerelease from the "
"next patch, minor, or major version respectively, such as `1.2.3 -> "
"1.3.0-rc.1` with `preminor` + `rc`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/semver.md:138
msgid ""
"Bumping within the same channel increments the sequence number, such as `"
"alpha.1 -> alpha.2`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/semver.md:140
msgid ""
"`release` removes prerelease and build metadata while keeping the same "
"`major.minor.patch` values, such as `1.2.3-rc.2 -> 1.2.3`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/semver.md:142
msgid ""
"Channel promotion is allowed (`alpha -> beta -> rc`), but channel downgrade "
"is not (for example, `rc -> beta` raises an error)."
msgstr ""
